FBIS4-60946 "drsov084_b_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-084 Daily Report 30 Apr 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Yeltsin Signs Edict To Streamline Use of Foreign Labor Yeltsin Signs Edict To Streamline Use of Foreign Labor LD3004140394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1328 GMT 30 Apr 94 LD3004140394 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [Text] Moscow April 30 TASS -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin signed a decree on Friday to streamline the use of foreign labour in Russia and ensure the priority right of Russian citizens to fill vacancies. The document expands the December 16, 1993 decree on the use of foreign labour in Russia to cover foreign legal entities operating in Russia under contracts. The new regulations will not apply to those organisations which send employees to Russia to install their equipment.
